  <summary>Steve McQueen: The Man &amp; Le Mans interweaves stunning newly discovered footage and voice recordings with original interviews. It is the true story of how a cinema legend would risk almost everything in pursuit of his dream.</summary>
  <reviews>
    <item index="0">
      <text>It's a great making-of tale about a very mediocre movie.</text>
      <source>Entertainment Weekly</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.ew.com/article/2015/11/17/steve-mcqueen-the-man-le-mans-ew-review</link>
      <author>Chris Nashawaty</author>
    </item>
    <item index="1">
      <text>If you see only one 44-years-later postmortem on a critical and commercial misfire this season, it might as well be "Steve McQueen: The Man &amp; Le Mans."</text>
      <source>Variety</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://variety.com/2015/film/reviews/steve-mcqueen-the-man-le-mans-review-1201639747/</link>
      <author>Joe Leydon</author>
    </item>
    <item index="2">
      <text>"Steve McQueen: The Man &amp; Le Mans" is an interesting documentary because it approaches its well-known subject from an unexpected angle.</text>
      <source>RogerEbert.com</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/steve-mcqueen-the-man-and-le-mans-2015</link>
      <author>Brian Tallerico</author>
    </item>
    <item index="3">
      <text>Filmmakers Gabriel Clarke and John McKenna interweave abundant archival footage and audio seamlessly.</text>
      <source>Los Angeles Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-steve-mcqueen-man-lemans-review-20151113-story.html</link>
      <author>Martin Tsai</author>
    </item>
    <item index="4">
      <text>It doesn't really succeed in conveying McQueen's great passion for auto racing. In truth, it mostly makes him seem like a jerk - but cinephiles might enjoy it as a case study of moviemaking gone wrong.</text>
      <source>New York Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/13/movies/review-steve-mcqueen-the-man-le-mans-a-documentary.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link>
      <author>Neil Genzlinger</author>
    </item>
    <item index="5">
      <text>We've seen many an insider doc about films destroyed by their creators' chutzpah (Overnight, Lost in La Mancha), but what's most wrenching here is McQueen's displays of vulnerability and tenderness.</text>
      <source>Village Voice</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.villagevoice.com/film/start-your-engines-for-the-vital-race-flick-doc-steve-mcqueen-the-man-and-le-mans-7885101</link>
      <author>Sam Weisberg</author>
    </item>
  </reviews>
